  BUG REPORTS

Bug #1: Misleading “X” icon in input fields

Description:
Red “X” icon appears in login input fields but is not interactive

Steps to Reproduce:
1.	Enter invalid login credentials
2.	Observe icon in input field

Expected Result:
Icon should either:
•	be clickable (clear input), OR
•	not appear as interactive

Actual Result:
Icon appears clickable but has no function

Severity:
Low

---

Bug #2: Filter dropdown arrow not responsive

Description:
Clicking the dropdown arrow does not open filter menu
Steps to Reproduce:
1.	Click directly on filter arrow icon

Expected Result:
Dropdown menu opens

Actual Result:
No response unless clicking center of dropdown

Severity:
Low / Medium

---

Bug #3: Unexpected logout when accessing product page

Description:
User is intermittently redirected to login page when accessing product details

Steps to Reproduce:
1.	Log in with valid credentials
2.	Navigate to product list
3.	Click on any product

Expected Result:
User remains logged in and views product details

Actual Result:
User is redirected to login page with message:
“You can only access '/inventory-item.html' when you are logged in.”

Severity:
High

Notes:
•	Issue occurs intermittently
•	Likely session handling issue

---

Bug #4: Filter selection not preserved

Description:
Selected filter resets after navigating back from product page

Steps to Reproduce:
1.	Apply a filter
2.	Open a product
3.	Return to product list

Expected Result:
Filter remains applied

Actual Result:
Filter resets to default

Severity:
Medium

---

  SUMMARY
The application performs well in core functionality such as login and cart operations. However, several usability and session-related issues were identified.
The most critical issue involves inconsistent session handling when navigating to product pages, which may impact user experience and trust.
Additional minor usability issues were observed in UI elements and filter interactions.

